JOHANNESBURG - South African singer Johnny Clegg died at the age of 66 after a long battle with pancreatic cancer. At the age of 17, together with Sipho Mchunu, they formed their first band called Juluka. In 1986, at the age of 33, during the height of Apartheid, he partnered with Dudu Zulu to form his second inter-racial band called Savuka. READ: SA musician Johnny Clegg has died Clegg also recorded several solo albums and enjoyed international success selling out concerts wherever he performed. He was diagnosed with pancreatic cancer in 2015 but continued to tour and perform around the world. Clegg received the Order of Ikhamanga as part of the national orders in 2012. eNCA.com has compiled a list of South African singer Johnny Clegg's top 5 music hits over the years Asimbonanga (Mandela) - Johnny Clegg & Savuka Johnny Clegg & Juluka - Impi Johnny Clegg Scatterlings Of Africa Johnny Clegg - Great Heart Johnny Clegg - "The Crossing"